\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs18\i\f1\noproof0\insrsid6635391 Reader:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid6635391   Praise the Lord from the heavens, praise Him in the highest.
\par  To Thee is due praise, O God.
\par 
\par Praise Him, all ye His angels; praise Him, all ye His hosts.
\par 
\par To Thee is due praise, O God.
\par 
\par Praise Him, O sun and moon; praise Him all ye stars and light.
\par 
\par Praise Him, ye heavens of heavens, and thou water that art above the heavens.
\par 
\par Let them praise the name of the Lord; for He spake, and they came to be; He commanded, and they were created.
\par 
\par He established them for ever, yea, for ever and ever; He hath set an ordinance, and it shall not pass away.
\par 
\par Praise the Lord from the earth, ye dragons, and all ye abysses.
\par 
\par Fire, hail, snow, ice, blast of tempest, which perform His word.
\par 
\par The mountains and all the hills, fruitful trees, and all cedars.
\par 
\par The beasts and all the cattle, creeping things and winged birds.
\par 
\par Kings of the earth, and all peoples, princes and all the judges of the earth.
\par 
\par Young men and virgins, elders with the younger; let them praise the name of the Lord, for exalted is the name of Him alone.
\par 
\par His praise is above the earth and heaven, and He shall exalt the horn of His people.
\par 
\par This is the hymn for all His saints, for the sons of Israel, and for the people that draw nigh unto Him.
\par 
\par Sing unto the Lord a new song; His praise is in the church of the saints.
\par 
\par Let Israel be glad in Him that made him, let the sons of Zion rejoice in their King.
\par 
\par Let them praise His name in the dance; with the timbrel and the psaltery let them chant unto Him.
\par 
\par For the Lord taketh pleasure in His people, and He shall exalt the meek with salvation.
\par 
\par The saints shall boast in glory, and they shall rejoice upon their beds.
\par 
\par The high praise of God shall be in their throat, and two-edged swords shall be in their hands.
\par 
\par To do vengeance among the heathen, punishments among the peoples.
\par 
\par To bind their kings with fetters, and their nobles with manacles of iron.
\par 
\par To do among them the judgment that is written.
\par  
\par This glory shall be to all His saints.
\par \~ 
\par Praise ye God in His saints, praise Him in the firmament of His power.
\par \~ 
\par Praise Him for His mighty acts, praise Him according to the multitude of His greatness.
\par 
\par Praise Him with the sound of trumpet, praise Him with the psaltery and harp.
\par 
\par Praise Him with timbrel and dance, praise him with strings and flute.
\par 
\par Praise Him with tuneful cymbals, praise Him with cymbals of jubilation. 
\par 
\par Let every breath praise the Lord.
\par \~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~ 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs24\b\i\fs28\insrsid6635391 Priest:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid6635391  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs19\b\fs36\noproof0\insrsid6635391 To Thee glory is due\'85
