\cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid6635391 
\par Lord, Thou hast been our refuge in generation and generation. 
\par 
\par Before the mountains came to be and the earth was formed and the world, even from everlasting to everlasting art Thou. 
\par 
\par Turn not man away unto lowliness; yea, Thou hast said: Turn back ye sons of men. 
\par 
\par For a thousand years in Thine eyes, O Lord, are but as yesterday that is past, and as a watch in the night. 
\par 
\par Things of no account shall their years be; in the morning like grass shall man pass away. In the morning shall he bloom and pass away. 
\par 
\par In the evening shall he fall and grow withered and dry. 
\par 
\par For we have fainted away in Thy wrath, and in Thine anger have we been troubled. 
\par Thou hast set our iniquities before us; our lifespan is in the light of Thy countenance. 
\par 
\par For all our days are faded away, and in Thy wrath are we fainted away; our years have, like a spider, spun out their tale. 
\par 
\par As for the days of our years, in their span, they be threescore years and ten. 
\par 
\par And if we be in strength, mayhap fourscore years; and what is more than these is toil and travail. 
\par 
\par For mildness is come upon us, and we shall be chastened. Who knoweth the might of Thy wrath? 
\par 
\par And out of fear of Thee, who can recount Thine anger? 
\par 
\par So make Thy right hand known to me, and to them that in their heart are instructed in wisdom. 
\par 
\par Return, O Lord; how long? 
\par 
\par And be Thou entreated concerning Thy servants. 
\par 
\par We were filled in the morning with Thy mercy, O Lord, and we rejoiced and were glad. 
\par 
\par In all our days, let us be glad for the days wherein Thou didst humble us, for the years wherein we saw evils. 
\par 
\par And look upon Thy servants, and upon Thy works, and do Thou guide their sons. 
\par 
\par 
\par And let the brightness of the Lord our God be upon us, and the works of our hands do Thou guide aright upon us, yea, the works of our hands do Thou guide aright.
\par 
