\par 
\par When wilt Thou come unto me? I have walked in the innocence of my heart in the midst of my house. 
\par 
\par I have no unlawful thing before mine eyes; the workers of transgressions I have hated. 
\par 
\par A crooked heart hath not cleaved unto me; as for the wicked man who turned from me, I knew him not. 
\par 
\par Him that privily talked against his neighbor did I drive away from me. With him whose eye was proud and his heart insatiate, I did not eat. 
\par 
\par Mine eyes were upon the faithful of the land, that they might sit with me; the man that walked in the blameless path, he ministered unto me. 
\par 
\par The proud doer dwelt not in the midst of my house; the speaker of unjust things prospered not before mine eyes. 
\par 
\par In the morning I slew all the sinners of the land, utterly to destroy out of the city of the Lord all them that work iniquity. 
\par 
\par Glory to the Father and to the Son and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
